event: Gets carried in her Moby Wrap
description: Mommy finally took the time to learn how to use the Moby. Symphony loved being snuggled so close. She took a nice long nap.
Symphony joined Mommy and Daddy on their anniversary date to see “The Greatest Showman.” She ended up peeing on mommy and then sleeping for the whole movie.

Touching Daddy’s beard is hilarious.

Symphony's self-awareness has really blossomed lately. Her latest discovery was her toes!
Symphony definitely prefers standing to lying down, so we bought her a jumper/bouncer. She loves it!
Symphony, after much tummy-time protesting, finally rolled over from tummy to back! She looked very confused at our enthusiasm.

event: Put binky in her own mouth
description: This is always a big one! Symphony has figured out how to put the binky in her own mouth the correct direction.
Symphony likes to pass toys from hand to hand! It’s pretty cute to watch.
Alas, Babykins has started waking up 2-3 times a night (usually 1 a.m. and 4 a.m.) to eat. Mommy is TIRED!
Symphony had her 6 month doctor visit today. She passed with flying colors! Yay!
Can finally get from being on her tummy to a sitting position! She is starting to get more mobile!!
Symphony crawled to try to reach baby Trinity Leckliter!
It’s official! This girl is moble and trying to eat everything she can find on the floor. Today, she turned her tongue hot pink by eating a post-it note.
Flew to Atlanta, GA with mommy and Angel for Southeast Homeschool Expo.
Not even crawling for two weeks, and she already figured out how to pull up to a stand. This kid is ready to move!
Harmony taught Symphony how to high five! She was very excited.

Learned to sign "more" when she wants more cereal bits.

event: Plays an active role in Peek-a-boo

description: It’s pretty cute to see her stick her hands up in the air.
She has started “stepping” while holding on to the couch or coffee table. I’m not ready for walking!!
Symphony briefly stood without holding on to anything (as Tony rewarded her with food each time)
Symphony crawled to the edge of a high bed, then turned around and safely lowered herself down.
Symphony took 5 or 6 steps to travel from one couch to another.
If someone tries to pick up Symphony while she is being held by mommy or daddy, she often aggressively shakes her head to say "No".
When Symphony wants to be held by any certain person, she points at him/her.
Symphony often points at Daddy and says "Dada!"
Symphony turned 1 year old today!
After a week-long visit with Grandpa and GrandMary, Symphony is now walking about 2/3 of the time. She can also stop and turn without falling over. So close to being a toddler!!

After hearing us say, “This?” after she points at what she wants (and us trying to guess) for several weeks, she now points and says, “This?” with the same inflection. Right now, “this” can mean anything from a cracker, to a toy, to the random object on the counter. It’s pretty cute.
Symphony, after watching us open the gate latch over and over, figured out how to open the latch and was halfway up the stairs before we figured out what happen. We caught her in video opening it up.
On Sunday, Jeremy started showing Symphony how to safely go down the stairs backwards. By Wednesday, she took the first open gate opportunity to try out her new skill.
Mommy decided to work on the sign for “please” when Symphony asked for a treat. She figured it out right away and within a week knew exactly what we meant. Good manners start early!
She created a game today of blowing in Daddy's face.
When finished eating, Symphony raised her hands to the sky and squeals "All done!"
Can very clearly say “ball”, but for fish she says “ish.”
Symphony is the baby ball and she cracks up whenever we play
Symphony ate about a dozen pieces of peaches using a fork to stab the peach pieces and left them to her mouth.
